member.name: F:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.BOMSchm.InsepAsPrt

member.name: P:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.BOMSchm.InsepPrmtsPrch

member.summary: Sets the life cycle state for a set of Items.
member.returns: The resulting Item changes along with warning and error restrictions.
member.param: The ID of the controlling Change Order.
An array of Item IDs.
The Life Cycle Definition ID of the new state.
If true, the child Items will also be updated to the new state. If false only the specified Items will change state.
If true, the Item will not bump revision when changing state. If false, the Item may bump revision based on the Item settings.
[out] Hard restrictions that occur on the specified Item and its immediate children. Hard restrictions mean that the operation failed and no data was changed.

[out] Soft restrictions that occur on children of the specified target Item. These can be overridden, if so desired, so long as the Item or its children do not have a restriction in optional restrictions as well.

[out] Hard restrictions that occur on children of Items flagged with warnings. If warnings are skipped, then these can be ignored. Otherwise, attempting to commit Items with warnings will fail with these restrictions.
[out] Items that can optionally be ignored or applied depending on warnings related to the items (as long as there are no optional restrictions for the item or it's children).

member.summary: Checks in a file to the Vault.
member.remarks: Upon check-in a new file must be uploaded and any dependencies must be re-specified. The file can also be renamed on check-in. If neither the file nor the associations have been altered, the checkin will be rolled back. In these cases, no error is thrown but the File object returned will be the rolled-back version.
member.returns: A File object representing the Vault's view of that file.
member.param: The masterId of the file being checking in.
Text data to be associated with the check-in.
If set to true, the new version gets uploaded and versioned, but the file is still checked out to the user.
The last time the file was modified on the client's machine.
The associations on the file.
A bill of materials to associate with this file. Null should be passed in if there is no BOM.
If this value is true and the 'bom' parameter is null, the BOM from the previous version will be copied for this version.
Allows the file to be renamed during the checkin.
The classification for the file.
A flag to indicate if a file should be hidden.
The binary contents the file. An empty byte array indicates a zero-length file. A null value indicates that the file data has not changed since the last version.

member.name: M:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.DocumentService.DeleteFileVersions(System.Int64[])
member.summary: Deletes specific versions of a file.
member.remarks: Even if a version meets all of the passed in criteria, it does not guarantee that the version will be deleted. Versions linked to Items will not be deleted. member.returns: A report of which versions have been deleted and which versions have not.
member.param: An array of file IDs to delete.

member.name: M:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.DocumentService.DeleteFileVersionsByMasterIds(System.Int64[],System.Boolean,System.Int32,System.Int32,System.String)
member.summary: Purges older versions of a file based on certian criteria.
member.remarks: Even if a version meets all of the passed in criteria, it does not guarantee that the version will be deleted. Versions linked to Items will not be deleted. Labeled or locked versions will not be deleted. Versions will not be deleted if they are linked to other versions which are not also being deleted. The most recent version cannot be deleted.
member.returns: A report of which versions have been deleted and which versions have not.
member.param: An array of File Masters IDs.
If false, all versions that can be purged are purged. If true, the versions purged are dependent on the next 3 parameters.

The number of versions to keep. Example: If there are 10 versions of a file and this value is 7, then only the first 3 versions will be deleted. This parameter is only used if deleteUncontrolledVersions is true.

The minimum age, in days, that a version has to be. Example: If this value is 60, then only versions older than 60 days will be deleted. This parameter is only used if deleteUncontrolledVersions is true.

Versions will not be deleted if this value is in the comment. Example: If this value is 'approved', then versions with the word 'approved' in the comment text will not be deleted. This parameter is only used if deleteUncontrolledVersions is true.

Likewise if an Enity has multiple links, they will all be returned if it matches the search criteria.

A list of folders to search in. This value pertains to the folder that the Link lives in, not the folder that the Entity lives in.

member.summary: Sets the life cycle state for a set of Items.
member.remarks: If the new state requires effectivity, use UpdateLifeCycleStatesAndEffectivity. Otherwise default effectivity (immediate start effectivity, no end effectivity) is used. See EditItemLifeCycleStates for an example code.
member.returns: The updated Items.
member.param: A set of Items.
The Life Cycle Definition ID of the new state.
If true, the child Items will also be updated to the new state. If false only the specified Items will change state.
[out] Hard restrictions that occur on the specified Item and its immediate children. Hard restrictions mean that the operation failed and no data was changed.

[out] Soft restrictions that occur on children of the specified target Item. These can be overridden, if so desired, so long as the Item or its children do not have a restriction in optional restrictions as well.

[out] Hard restrictions that occur on children of Items flagged with warnings. If warnings are skipped, then these can be ignored. Otherwise, attempting to commit Items with warnings will fail with these restrictions.
[out] Items that can optionally be ignored or applied depending on warnings related to the items (as long as there are no optional restrictions for the item or it's children).

member.name: M:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.KnowledgeVaultService.GetMaximumFileSize
member.summary: Gets the maximum size for a file upload.
member.remarks: The maximum file size is actually a little less than the value indicated. This is because the XML data in the web service call is also counted as part of the maximum size. This value can be changed by modifying the maxRequestLength parameter in the web.config file, which is in the Server\Web\Services directory of a Vault server install. The maximum value allowed is 2 GB. It is not necessary to call SignIn2 prior to calling this function.
member.returns: The maximum size file (in kilobytes) allowed for upload. In a default installation, this value is 51200 KB.

member.name: M:Autodesk.Connectivity.WebServices.KnowledgeVaultService.GetSiteCompatibilityWithKnowledgeMaster
member.summary: Tells if the Knowledge Master of the current site is compatible with the database.
member.remarks: Each install of ADMS is tagged with version information which must synch up with the version information in the ADMS database. If a new version of ADMS is installed, but the databases have not yet been migrated, then things are in an incompatible state. This function is also useful multi-site environments to see if a site needs to be upgraded to a newer version of ADMS.
member.returns: Tells if the site is compatible or not. If it is not compatible, extra information is provided on the conflicts.
